javmos

Class Polynomial

  • java.lang.Object
    • javmos.Polynomial

  • public class Polynomial
extends java.lang.Object
    This class calculates key properties of a polynomial and uses them to draw it. You cannot add any other methods nor modify the method signatures.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Polynomial

        public Polynomial(JavmosGUI gui,
                  java.lang.String polynomial)
           throws PolynomialException
        Primary class constructor.
        Parameters:
        gui - An instance of the JavmosGUI.
        polynomial - A String representation of the polynomial written in terms of y or f(x). Terms can be in mixed order and there are no spaces between them. The degrees of 0 and 1 degree terms are not typed. For example: f(x)=5x^7-2x+3+5x^2
        Throws:
        PolynomialException - An exception thrown if the user inputs an invalid polynomial expression.

      • getRoots

        public java.util.HashSet<Point> getRoots(RootType rootType,
                                         double minDomain,
                                         double maxDomian)
        This method returns a HashSet of the unique roots of this polynomial rounded to nearest thousandth. DecimalFormat will be useful for rounding; use the HALF_DOWN mode. Be mindful of the -0 result for both the x and y coordinates.
        Parameters:
        rootType - An enum representing the type of root being calculated.
        minDomain - The minimum domain for which the roots are to be calculated.
        maxDomian - The maximum domain for which the roots are to be calculated.
        Returns:
        Returns a HashSet of the unique roots of this polynomial rounded to nearest thousandth.
        See Also:
        DecimalFormat

      • newtonsMethod

        public java.lang.Double newtonsMethod(RootType rootType,
                                      double guess,
                                      int attempts)
        This private method is to be recursively written and returns the root if found, otherwise returns null. Be mindful of NaN results and if the degree of a polynomial is 0 or less.
        Parameters:
        rootType - An enum representing the type of root being calculated.
        guess - The initial guess for Netwon's method.
        attempts - The number of attempts before Newtons' method returns null.
        Returns:
        Returns the root if found, otherwise returns null.
        See Also:
        RootType
